@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy</PageTitle>

<div style="max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 20px;">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: @lastUpdated.ToString("d MMMM yyyy")</em></p>

    <p>
        This notice explains how Lanyard handles personal data within the Lanyard Staff and CRM System. The data controller is Lanyard / Benjamin Mercer. For any privacy questions or to
        exercise your rights, contact   
        <a href="mailto:benmercer76@btinternet.com">benmercer76@btinternet.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>What we process</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Staff account details: username, email, name, date of birth, preferred language, and a hashed password.</li>
        <li>Attendance records: clock-in/out times, shifts, and rota assignments.</li>
        <li>Device and network data: client device IP addresses and network interface addresses.</li>
        <li>Security logs, which may include IP addresses.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Why, and our legal basis</h2>
    <p>
        We process this data to manage staff access, to keep working-time records (a legal
        obligation and part of your employment), and to operate and secure our venue systems (our
        legitimate interests).
    </p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>
        We keep personal data only as long as necessary for these purposes and to meet legal
        obligations. Retention periods are set out in our internal data-retention policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
        You have the right to access, correct, erase, or restrict processing of your personal
        data, and to object to processing. To exercise these, contact
        <a href="mailto:benmercer76@btinternet.com">benmercer76@btinternet.com</a>. You may also complain to
        the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO).
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
        Lanyard uses only strictly-necessary cookies: an authentication cookie to keep you signed
        in (up to 14 days) and an antiforgery token to protect forms. These are essential to the
        service and are not used for tracking or analytics.
    </p>
</div>

@code {
    private DateTime lastUpdated = new DateTime(2026, 7, 16);
}